<br />
<br />I suspect that the interface is working OK.  What may not be OK is the drive-  either it's bad,  it does not like CDRs (did you use a CDR or CDRW?), or the image is bad.
<br />
<br />If the interface wasn't working right, I suspect it would've failed to work at all.  It sounds like it got pretty far- asked for a disk, accepted disk, spun it up, then read from it.  That most likely means the interface works.

		

