		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Any particular reason you're burning at 1X?  I'd say to burn at maximum speed on the cheapest CD-R available, just because that would be what the burner is designed towards.
<br />
<br />But if these old drives can't read any CD-Rs, that would suck.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /> 
<br />I don't think they're as reflective as pressed CDs, and CD-RWs even less so.
<br />
<br />If it's any help, I have an old CD-ROM + soundcard interface stashed away somewhere (I'm guessing it's MKE) that I could do some kind of test with.  I'm kinda out of CD-Rs at the moment, though I could probably scrounge one up.  I already have an old PC set up anyways.

		

