		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For windows apps I recommend Cdrwin by Golden Hawk Technology or ImgBurn by Lightning UK. CDmage can help you examine images and ISOBuster can help you examine a CD without making an image if you need to test the disc type.
<br />
<br />When I last used my GDSF CDROM, I'm pretty sure I used Nero to create and burn the disc.

		

